JavaScript is a client side scripting language.
It is used to make web pages alive.
It is used to programmatically perform actions within the page.
When JavaScript was created, it was initially called "LiveScript".
DOM -Document Object Model.
JavaScript is a younger bro of JAVA.
**> IN-BROWSER JAVASCRIPT:-
we can use javascript as a client as well as server side language.
It can used to perform wide variety of tasks.
 Ajax requests.
 Get and set cookies and local storage.
**> In-Browser JavaScript can't do these things:-
-Read/Write to and from Computer Hard disk.
